PlainText.TextValue: ToD: Review and approve all entries by accounting dual report

Review journal entries for the following: • They are only entered by authorized personnel and in accordance with the authorized segregation of duties table. • Ensure that non-recurring or unusual items above a certain monetary threshold, as defined by each reporting entity have been reviewed and approved by the A&R Dual Report. • That discrepancies are investigated and evidence of the review is maintained.

Review on a sample basis before submission to CC. A&R analytical reviews performed on the balance sheet and profit and loss accounts, both on the general ledger level, as well as on the IRP level: • Check that all large movements or variations from the budget from one year to the next have been fully explained. • Check that entries over 12 months old are still valid • Check that each account is the responsibility of a current employee, who performs a regular reconciliation of the balance.

Review all suspense accounts and check that: • All entries represent either unexplained items under investigation or items in transit • Unexplained items are not older than 12 months • Items in transit are not older than 1 month

The Accounting Dual Report reviews and approves (by signing either individual or in the aggregate)
all entries for non-recurring or unusual items above a certain monetary threshold, as defined by each
reporting entity. If the Accounting Dual Report needs more information regarding certain entries
he/she discusses this with the preparers. General ledger accounts, including any suspense accounts,
should be analyzed and reviewed for unusual items and details of the review process should be
documented as well as the results of these procedures (including follow up on differences if
required). Refer to Appendix A “Considerations for Analytical Review Procedures” - to ensure
financial data is accurate and Journal entries are authorized

System has acceptance rules for journal entries

Journal entries are only accepted into the system if: (i) they balance, (ii) the account numbers used are valid and (iii) all required fields are entered – to prevent unauthorized, inaccurate or incomplete journal entries being booked.
